What do you mean it's not an inconvenience to the police or fire department?

216
00:18:49,130 --> 00:18:50,693
They can get right there.

217
00:18:50,994 --> 00:18:52,177
They are right there.

218
00:18:52,537 --> 00:18:54,501
They can be there in a minute to render.

219
00:18:54,622 --> 00:18:57,989
That's not the purpose of police to fire, not to respond to the call.

220
00:18:58,009 --> 00:19:00,053
Our job is to prevent the accident.

221
00:19:00,813 --> 00:19:05,436
Okay, you can do as much as you can to prevent accidents.

222
00:19:05,716 --> 00:19:09,618
You're not gonna prevent accidents as long as cars are traveling on the roadways.

223
00:19:10,058 --> 00:19:25,027
So to say it's a safety issue and we'll just cut off the access is not looking at alternative or lesser measures, okay, to continue the flow of traffic and to provide access roads for people that live in your community and pay taxes.

224
00:19:25,727 --> 00:19:28,487
That's the point I'm trying to make, okay?

225
00:19:28,768 --> 00:19:30,828
That you're not looking at the lesser alternatives.

226
00:19:30,848 --> 00:19:33,368
You did put a sign there.

227
00:19:33,688 --> 00:19:35,709
You put the wrong one, okay?

228
00:19:35,749 --> 00:19:46,731
You need to put a flashing neon intersection sign, not a stop sign, not a traffic control signal or anything, which costs a lot of money, okay?

229
00:19:46,751 --> 00:19:47,551
They're yellow.

230
00:19:47,651 --> 00:19:52,372
They're usually diamond or actually, I don't know what they call them.

231
00:19:53,012 --> 00:19:54,712
They're diamond shaped or something.

232
00:19:55,329 --> 00:20:06,580
and they flash their yellow and their neon, and that will attract the attention of drivers that approach that intersection to slow down, and you will reduce the collisions.

233
00:20:07,501 --> 00:20:13,848
That is an alternative to doing this, which is just to cut off the intersection completely.

234
00:20:14,574 --> 00:20:21,618
All right, we are a, in Metcalfe Street, we are a one-way street to a one-way street to a one-way street.

235
00:20:21,678 --> 00:20:24,599
We are a series of intersecting one-way streets.

236
00:20:25,259 --> 00:20:33,684
And you are making it very difficult on a huge section of your neighborhood, which is Medford Hillside, okay, to gain access to these roadways.

237
00:20:34,649 --> 00:20:36,710
Okay, now you've already cut off two of them.

238
00:20:36,770 --> 00:20:44,691
Why don't you just leave this one alone and make some lesser alternatives to keep the road going?

239
00:20:44,711 --> 00:20:46,132
All right, thank you.

240
00:20:46,152 --> 00:20:47,612
You don't have to just cut it off.

241
00:20:47,652 --> 00:20:51,173
We've had the traffic engineer review a lot of the things that you've talked about.

242
00:20:51,313 --> 00:20:58,135
And in his opinion, closing it off is the recommended avenue for prevention.

243
00:20:58,995 --> 00:21:03,276
We did deal with South Street, South Street and Main Street.

244
00:21:04,461 --> 00:21:11,486
consistently one of the worst intersections for motor vehicle accidents with injuries in the state year after year.

245
00:21:12,527 --> 00:21:16,409
We've come up with a solution, and there's a long-term solution associated with that.

246
00:21:16,790 --> 00:21:20,732
There have been very few, if any, motor vehicle accidents since we put that in place.

247
00:21:21,213 --> 00:21:24,535
This is a little bit more about convenience and inconvenience.

248
00:21:24,655 --> 00:21:27,197
It's about safety and people getting hurt.

249
00:21:27,877 --> 00:21:31,039
A simple sign isn't necessarily what the engineers recommend.

250
00:21:32,060 --> 00:21:36,066
I understand if you need to get to Medford Square, you can still come out South Street.

251
00:21:36,687 --> 00:21:39,812
It's much safer and there is an avenue to take a left-hand turn.

252
00:21:40,253 --> 00:21:45,521
If you need to get to 93, you can do the same and head into Medford Square and jump on 93.

253
00:21:46,607 --> 00:21:51,031
You can also take a right on Main Street and head down Mr. Gap and get on 93.

254
00:21:51,691 --> 00:21:56,935
Or you could go down Main Street to the right and take one of the left-hand turns and come back on Mr. Gap.

255
00:21:57,416 --> 00:21:58,036
I understand.

256
00:21:58,056 --> 00:22:03,340
I'm not telling you that that is an inconvenience, and I'm not telling you that it's not a change, but it is safer.

257
00:22:04,181 --> 00:22:07,003
And that is what our job is.

258
00:22:07,103 --> 00:22:07,604
Next comment.

259
00:22:07,884 --> 00:22:08,204
Siding.

260
00:22:09,005 --> 00:22:10,886
David Asher is next.

261
00:22:11,427 --> 00:22:12,948
Mr. Asher, just unmute yourself.

