00:33:13,265 --> 00:33:23,688
Now, if there's some other way that you've gotten your numbers, I think your numbers were much more higher than that for Emerson Street.

383
00:33:23,728 --> 00:33:26,629
I don't know where you get it and the public doesn't.

384
00:33:27,569 --> 00:33:28,990
But that's...

385
00:33:30,275 --> 00:33:31,135
That's my homework.

386
00:33:31,155 --> 00:33:31,895
That's what I've done.

387
00:33:32,976 --> 00:33:36,496
It's not just a resident problem.

388
00:33:36,536 --> 00:33:41,797
It's a big resident problem, sure, but just a city problem.

389
00:33:42,137 --> 00:33:44,858
And then that is, oh, let me speak to the navigation part.

390
00:33:45,838 --> 00:33:49,379
When you turn on a navigation software, it takes you the shortest route.

391
00:33:49,479 --> 00:33:53,880
So if South Street is blocked up with cars, that becomes a red zone.

392
00:33:55,491 --> 00:33:58,553
and they're gonna tell you to go down Emerson Street because it's quicker.

393
00:33:59,174 --> 00:34:03,197
Now, programs like Waze, even Google, it's not one.

394
00:34:03,357 --> 00:34:07,560
Any kind of navigation app you have is going to tell you to go the shortest route.

395
00:34:08,361 --> 00:34:18,649
And again, this is a driver problem or a pedestrian problem because you've got people, like I said, if they're on two feet, two wheels, four wheels, it doesn't matter, they're people.

396
00:34:19,049 --> 00:34:22,092
And this is people making bad decisions.

397
00:34:23,677 --> 00:34:25,300
and not being courteous to one another.

398
00:34:25,420 --> 00:34:29,025
And of course, it's going to create a safety problem.

399
00:34:29,125 --> 00:34:35,154
So that's not something that we can control by any blockage lights or signs or anything.

400
00:34:35,514 --> 00:34:36,976
That's just going to keep happening.

401
00:34:38,180 --> 00:34:50,908
But what can happen, the most inexpensive and now thing to do at that corner is to put a physical person out there during peak hours to direct traffic.

402
00:34:51,609 --> 00:34:52,269
It's very simple.

403
00:34:52,309 --> 00:34:54,411
You have them at dig sites.

404
00:34:54,431 --> 00:34:55,731
You have them in front of schools.

405
00:34:56,892 --> 00:35:04,137
Why not just put them in these problem areas for a few hours in the morning and a few hours in the evening and just

406
00:35:05,333 --> 00:35:10,678
make people stop and let people cross the street, let people get out, take their left turn, etc, etc.

407
00:35:11,860 --> 00:35:15,863
It's been done that way since cars were invented and cities were invented.

408
00:35:16,504 --> 00:35:18,106
Just have a traffic cop out there.

409
00:35:18,846 --> 00:35:19,627
That's all you have to do.

410
00:35:19,667 --> 00:35:20,428
That's all I have to say.

411
00:35:20,448 --> 00:35:23,311
I appreciate your comments and

412
00:35:26,295 --> 00:35:27,335
the way you've placed it.

413
00:35:27,536 --> 00:35:28,156
I think Sgt.

414
00:35:28,176 --> 00:35:31,937
Craver has a comment on the statistics that we pulled.

